# MHFT Design System Consistency

- Use existing color, spacing, typography, and radius tokens before adding new values.
- Keep section rhythm consistent with balanced whitespace and predictable vertical spacing.
- Prefer modern, minimal component styling with restrained shadows and borders.
- Maintain visual clarity with strong typographic hierarchy and concise copy blocks.
- Reuse established CTA variants and interaction states across pages.
- Avoid introducing new visual motifs unless they improve consistency site-wide.
